  "prompt": "Which is the best haircut for man?",
  "response": "The best haircut for a man depends on several factors, including face shape, hair type, personal style, and lifestyle. Here are some popular haircuts that can suit various preferences:\n\n1. **Crew Cut**: A classic and low-maintenance option, ideal for those with a busy lifestyle.\n\n2. **Undercut**: Features short sides and longer hair on top, allowing for versatile styling.\n\n3. **Fade**: A gradual transition from short to longer hair, which can be combined with various styles on top.\n\n4. **Pompadour**: A stylish option with volume on top and shorter sides, great for a polished look.\n\n5. **Buzz Cut**: Very short and clean, perfect for a minimalist style.\n\n6. **Textured Crop**: Suitable for thicker hair, this cut adds texture and can be styled messily.\n\n7. **Side Part**: A classic look that works well for professional settings and can be styled with varying lengths.\n\n8. **Longer Styles**: If you prefer longer hair, consider styles like a man bun or shoulder-length cuts, depending on your hair type and maintenance preferences.\n\nIt's best to consult with a hairstylist who can recommend a cut that complements your features and hair type.",
